- What are you doing with that butt?
- Oh, you've embarrassed me now.

19:58.200 --> 20:03.593
It's just that your lips have touched it.
The king's kissing lips!

20:03.680 --> 20:08.879
I just wanted some proof that I'd
actually met the Duke of Deliciousness!

20:08.960 --> 20:11.190
You're serious, aren't you?

20:11.280 --> 20:13.999
- Serious about what?
- I'm a nobody!

20:14.080 --> 20:19.438
Out of 169 people aboard this ship,
I ranked 169. Bottom of the pile.

20:19.520 --> 20:22.592
That's because you didn't want that career stuff.

20:22.680 --> 20:26.514
You wanted your farm on Fi ji
with you-know-who.

20:26.600 --> 20:28.591
- If she'd come.
- If?!

20:28.680 --> 20:33.117
And turn down the opportunity
of becoming the envy of all womankind?

20:33.200 --> 20:36.272
- Oh, we'll never know now.
- Why not?

20:36.360 --> 20:38.920
- She's dead.
- So is Rimmer.

20:39.000 --> 20:43.312
Holly can only sustain one hologram,
and Rimmer's hidden the personality disks.

20:43.400 --> 20:46.039
- So? Find them.
- I can't.

20:46.120 --> 20:50.193
King, you can do anything.

20:50.280 --> 20:52.077
Anything!

20:52.280 --> 20:56.910
- .. anything. He can't do anything.
- Oh, I know. I'll bet five.

20:57.000 --> 20:59.912
He used to practise kissing on his own.

21:00.000 --> 21:03.037
- How?
- He made lips out of one hand,

21:03.120 --> 21:06.908
then waggled his thumb
through the gap like a tongue.

21:07.920 --> 21:10.150
That is priceless.

21:10.240 --> 21:14.074
Seventeen years old
and he snogged his own hand.

21:14.160 --> 21:19.518
Once, in front of the whole school,
he called his gym teacher "Daddy".

21:19.600 --> 21:21.750
I could've died with embarrassment.

21:21.840 --> 21:24.229
What a silly thing to do.

21:24.320 --> 21:29.155
- I hate him.
- Then why talk about him so much?

21:29.240 --> 21:33.119
Because he makes my life
one big, humiliating, cringe-making,

21:33.200 --> 21:35.191
guilt-ridden hell!

21:35.280 --> 21:37.999
Now! Stab him! Stab him! Stab him!

21:39.160 --> 21:44.792
Ah, you haven't met Stabhim.
He's one of our skutters.

21:44.880 --> 21:49.351
Stabhim, meet Lister's paranoia.
Lister's paranoia, this is Stabhim.

21:49.440 --> 21:51.431
Yo, Rimmer, we've been thinking.

21:51.520 --> 21:54.910
We might get Kochanski back
without turning you off.

21:55.000 --> 21:58.231
Oh, he's drunk. I can smell it from here.

21:58.320 --> 22:02.552
If we turn off all unnecessary systems,
Holly says it'll work.

22:02.640 --> 22:06.838
Another great idea from the people
who brought you beer milkshakes!

22:06.920 --> 22:09.798
You're obsessed with a girl you hardly know.

22:09.880 --> 22:13.509
Hardly knows her?
You haven't heard the "indling" song!

22:13.600 --> 22:16.990
- # Our love I tried to kindle... #
- Not now!

22:17.720 --> 22:20.712
- You're not having her disk.
- Because she'll outrank you?

22:20.800 --> 22:25.271
But she's a bright, good-looking,
witty, upwardly mobile officer.

22:25.360 --> 22:27.669
Why should she fancy you?

22:27.760 --> 22:31.389
- Yes, why should she fancy you?
- Yeah, why should she?

22:31.480 --> 22:34.836
Hmm? Sorry, I was just thinking
about that song.

22:34.920 --> 22:39.436
I can't get it out of my head.
Why? Because you're great!

22:39.520 --> 22:42.557
You're an incredibly seductive,
charming, charismatic young stud!

22:42.640 --> 22:45.438
Yeah, I forgot. That's why.

22:45.520 --> 22:48.273
You're not having her disk or any disk.

22:48.360 --> 22:51.397
Come on, King. Where would he hide 'em?

22:51.480 --> 22:53.869
- I don't know.
- Yes, you do.

22:53.960 --> 22:57.748
- No, he doesn't.
- Come on, think "winner".

22:59.440 --> 23:01.749
Outside. Outside the ship.

23:02.760 --> 23:06.355
- Er, wrong, actually!
- Where outside?

23:06.440 --> 23:09.671
Well, he'd have to send the skutters...

23:09.760 --> 23:13.036
Wrong, wrong! Absolutely brimming
over with wrongability.

23:13.120 --> 23:17.432
They'd have to be under my nose,
so he could laugh.

23:17.520 --> 23:20.080
Wrong and getting wronger all the time.

23:20.160 --> 23:22.549
Outside our sleeping quarters.

23:22.640 --> 23:25.393
The solar panel outside our sleeping quarters!

23:25.480 --> 23:28.074
You followed me, you goit!

23:28.200 --> 23:30.998
Is that where they are?! That's incredible! I did it!

23:34.960 --> 23:36.757
Lister?

23:45.360 --> 23:48.272
- How long now, Hol?
- Can't be long, Dave,

23:48.360 --> 23:50.828
Hercule has the suspects in one room,

23:50.920 --> 23:54.037
and I'm two pages from "by the same author",

23:54.120 --> 23:56.315
No, Holly. The dust storm.

23:56.400 --> 23:59.710
Oh, that,
Any time now, it's almost subsided,

23:59.800 --> 24:04.715
Yeah, how's my baby boy?
You've got a body like a coat hanger!

24:04.800 --> 24:07.712
You make a spacesuit look like eveningwear.

24:07.800 --> 24:12.112
- Let me ask you one question?
- It's no use arguing. I'm going.

24:12.200 --> 24:15.954
- Who smashed up the medicomp?
- He's stalling, King. Let's go.

24:16.040 --> 24:18.474
Holly, give him a punch up.

24:18.560 --> 24:21.233
Why would they smash it up?

24:21.320 --> 24:24.437
Lister, come here. Come here.

24:26.480 --> 24:28.471
You are still sick.

24:28.560 --> 24:30.835
- I feel great.
- You will not...

24:31.840 --> 24:33.831
You will not...

24:33.920 --> 24:37.549
You will not be better until they've gone.

24:37.640 --> 24:41.394
They know that, and they've stopped you
getting any treatment.

24:42.920 --> 24:44.911
Where's Paranoia?

24:45.000 --> 24:48.231
I don't know. Is it someplace near Uruguay?

24:48.320 --> 24:50.311
Who is this joker?

24:50.400 --> 24:54.188
- They're germs and they're dangerous.
- The storm has passed, Dave,

24:54.280 --> 24:58.717
- Airlocks are now released,
- What are we waiting for, King?

24:58.800 --> 25:00.597
Nothing.

25:01.720 --> 25:05.998
- Holly, put a trace on Paranoia.
- What's a trace?

25:06.080 --> 25:10.756
- It's space jargon. It means find him.
- You made that up to be cool,

25:11.400 --> 25:15.837
- Where is he?
- Paranoia is no longer on this ship,

25:18.120 --> 25:20.395
Look at that view, Kingo!

25:20.480 --> 25:23.995
On top of the world! Makes you wanna dance!

25:24.080 --> 25:26.071
# Cha, cha-cha

25:26.160 --> 25:27.673
# Cha-cha, cha-cha cha-cha

25:27.760 --> 25:29.716
# Cha, cha-cha

25:29.800 --> 25:31.870
# Cha-cha, cha-cha cha-cha #

25:31.960 --> 25:34.076
Hey, here it is!

25:34.160 --> 25:36.151
# Cha-cha,
cha-cha, cha-cha, cha-cha... #

25:44.360 --> 25:46.351
- Did you hear something?
- Nope.

25:46.440 --> 25:51.116
- In space, no one can hear you cha-cha!
- Could Paranoia be here?

25:51.200 --> 25:54.158
- Forget him.
- He smashed up the medical unit.

25:54.240 --> 25:57.596
- No, he didn't. I did.
- You did?

25:57.680 --> 26:01.719
So we can be together. I did it for you!

26:01.800 --> 26:04.360
- Where did he go, then?
- I killed him.

26:04.440 --> 26:07.000
What do you mean, you killed him?!

26:07.080 --> 26:11.517
Hey, he didn't suffer.
I fed him into the waste grinder

26:11.600 --> 26:14.068
and flushed his bits into space.

26:14.160 --> 26:17.072
Look, I'm gonna go inside now.

26:17.160 --> 26:20.357
Gets a little claustrophobic in these suits.

26:20.440 --> 26:22.590
- Take your helmet off.
- What?!

26:22.680 --> 26:25.911
- Take your helmet off.
- I'll die. There's no oxygen!

26:26.000 --> 26:30.312
- Hey, oxygen's for losers. Come on!
- I need oxygen!

26:30.400 --> 26:34.029
You don't need anything. You're the king!

26:34.120 --> 26:37.271
- You're crazy!
- Who told you you needed oxygen?

26:37.360 --> 26:40.591
Some loser trying to make you feel small.

26:40.680 --> 26:44.355
I'll prove it to you. I'll take mine off first.

26:44.440 --> 26:47.477
- We'll see who's crazy around here!
- No!

27:00.520 --> 27:03.034
- Must you do this now?
- I'm doing my laundry!

27:03.120 --> 27:06.430
- It's totally disgusting.
- What's disgusting?

27:11.440 --> 27:13.431
- Lister.
- Yeah?

27:13.520 --> 27:16.637
I just want to say I was right all along.

27:16.720 --> 27:20.793
- I said they were germs and they were.
- OK. So what?

27:20.880 --> 27:24.395
And I'm saying that disk will bring you misery.

27:24.480 --> 27:26.710
Just remember I said that.

27:26.800 --> 27:31.237
If she comes back and she's not interested,
I can handle it.

27:31.320 --> 27:35.791
Whatever, Lister. That disk
is a one-way ticket to Miseryville.

27:35.880 --> 27:38.838
I spent enough time listening to me paranoia.

27:38.920 --> 27:41.115
Now I'm listening to me confidence.

27:55.840 --> 27:58.400
Hi, Krissie... It's not gonna work.

27:58.480 --> 28:02.075
Hello, Krissie... That's not gonna work either.

28:02.160 --> 28:04.720
Hey! Yo! Krissie!

28:05.440 --> 28:06.953
Hi...

28:12.320 --> 28:15.517
Lister, good luck. I mean it.

28:15.600 --> 28:18.512
- Smeg off.
- No, honestly. Good luck.

28:18.600 --> 28:21.319
OK, Hol. Switch it on.

28:23.920 --> 28:26.832
- Well, he did warn you.
- I certainly did.

28:26.920 --> 28:31.391
Do you honestly think I'd put
Kochanski's disk in Kochanski's box

28:31.480 --> 28:33.789
where any munchkin could find it?

28:33.880 --> 28:37.111
You think you had it bad before, Lister?

28:37.200 --> 28:40.636
Well, now you've got it in stereo, baby.

28:41.840 --> 28:46.436
- Welcome aboard, Rimmsie.
- Nice to be here, you son of a gun.

28:50.520 --> 28:52.317
# It's cold outside

28:52.400 --> 28:54.197
# There's no kind of atmosphere

28:54.280 --> 28:57.636
# I'm all alone, more or less

28:57.720 --> 29:00.837
# Let me fly far away from here

29:00.920 --> 29:03.673
# Fun, fun, fun

29:03.760 --> 29:07.275
# In the sun, sun, sun

29:07.360 --> 29:10.716
# I want to lie, shipwrecked and comatose

29:10.800 --> 29:14.076
# Drinking fresh mango juice

29:14.160 --> 29:17.436
# Goldfish shoals, nibbling at my toes

29:17.520 --> 29:20.193
# Fun, fun, fun

